      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET SURRENDER (1) went from 1400m to 2000m at Belmont last start and was too good, winning by 0.3L when rounding up her rivals. She is a lightly raced mare and still has some room to grow. Cooper's claim comes in handy and with further improvement in store, she can repeat the dose. POINTLESS PRAISE (3) is ticking along nicely without winning, missing by 2.3L last time out but he finds a suitable race here. Should be able to lob in a handy position from gate 5 and he'll get every chance to put his best foot forward. SHAULA (2) is right in this on his recent efforts, finishing 1.3L off the winner at Belmont. He was behind sweet surrender there but he gets a weight swing in his favour and he can feature in the finish. SECRICITY (4) steps out in distance today and can get back to winning ways on the quick turnaround. GRANDAD'S ADICTION (9) can bounce back to form with the rise in trip.",
